<HEADLINE>
SON OF HONG KONG BUSINESS TYCOON VISITS TAICHUNG
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, March 17 (CNA) 03/18/07  11:42:43 (By Maubo Chang)
</P>
<P>
Richard Li Tzar Kai, son of Hong Kong business tycoon Li Ka-Shing
and chairman of PCCW Limited in Hong Kong arrived in Taichung,
central Taiwan for a private visit Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Li, who came aboard a train of the Taipei High Speed Rail from
Taoyuan after flying in at the Taiwan Taoyuan International
Airport, was whisked to the residence of Taichung Mayor Jason Hu.
</P>
<P>
He told journalists afterward that he has known Hu and his wife
Shirley Shao for more than 20 years, and he is pleased to see
</P>
<P>
Shao recover quite well from injuries she suffered in a terrible
traffic accident last November.
</P>
<P>
Li attended a dinner party host by Hu in his honor Saturday night
and met with many local estate developers, but he refused to say
whether he is interested in investing in property in this central
Taiwan city.
</P>
<P>
Stressing his visit is a private one, Li refused to disclose his
itinerary in Taiwan but a local TV station said he will tour the
Sun Moon Lake in Nantou Sunday.
</P>
